Name: Air Jordan 4 Retro Se Sneakers
Description: The Air Jordan 4 Air Max 95 Neon is a special Air Max month release of Michael Jordans fourth signature basketball sneaker that honors the equally legendary Air Max 95 Neon colorway. The Air Max 95 Neon debuted in 1995 as the flagship design of the highly innovative performance running sneaker that instantly became popular thanks to its appealing looks, top flight comfort, and first-ever visible forefoot Air. Now, the ahead-of-its-time design finds its way to the Air Jordan 4 and the results are favorable. Donning the upper is the same gradient grey color scheme of the Air Max 95 that features various shades of the neutral color starting from light at the collar and gradually getting darker as it works down to the midsole. Bright neon accenting along the netted panel, eyelets, and Jumpman branding on the tongue and heel add 90s-era contrasting to the silhouette. Finishing off the look is a black rubber midsole with a visible neon-tinted Air unit in the heel.

Name: Air Jordan 3 Retro Sneakers
Description: Supplied by a premier sneaker marketplace dealing with unworn, already sold out, in demand rarities. Each product is rigorously inspected by experienced experts guaranteeing authenticity. The Air Jordan 3 UNC is a Carolina-blue-based colorway of the Jordan 3 design inspired by the University of North Carolina Tarheels. The UNC makeup of the Air Jordan 3 first arrived as a player exclusive during the 2018 NCAA Mens March Madness Basketball Tournament and now re-appears as a separate release for the general public. Similar to the PE version, the retail Air Jordan 3 UNC features a white tumbled leather base that includes hits on the toe and mid-panel. Contrasting along the mudguard comes in the form of Air Jordan 3-specific elephant print on the toe, lateral panel, and heel that contrasts a solid white leather mudguard. Completing the look is black Jumpman branding on the heel and a light grey outsole. Release date: Spring 2020.
